  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The equation&nbsp;<math alttext=\"h equals StartFraction 9 left parenthesis v minus 273.15 right parenthesis Over 5 EndFraction plus 32\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>273.15</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>32</mn></math> gives the corresponding temperature <math alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi>\n</math>, in degrees Fahrenheit, of any substance that has a temperature of <math alttext=\"v\"><mi>v</mi>\n</math> kelvins, where <math alttext=\"v greater than 0\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. If a substance has a temperature of <math alttext=\"467.33\"><mn>467.33</mn>\n</math> degrees Fahrenheit, what is the corresponding temperature, in kelvins, of this substance?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
